entries.femaleVariant: Nuh-uh, no passage. Get lost.
I said – no passage.
Back off, or it'll be hands, not words.
Why take any risks? C'mon, we don't have time.
Bet anything you'll find a power source inside.
Just follow the pointers I'm showin' you.
Head down, stay outta sight.
Elevator – hop in. I'll do the rest.
Bright as the cityside metro, huh?
Doin' the opposite of what I say on purpose, V, really?
Hey, hey, pipe down. Already got one holowhiner in my head, don't need another.
Not that way, V.
Back to the side entrance, go.
That was you?!
Better than Bartmoss…
No shit, that was you?! Only the best reach that high. Talkin' Spider Murphy, Bartmoss…
Ah, didn't hit it off with Johnny, did you?
Apologize up front for the query, but I gotta ask... Konpeki Plaza heist – why?
Hop on the platform. I'll guide you to the garage from there.
Told you they wouldn't let you in.
You! Got cyberwheels or something? Feet on the sidewalk, now.
'Ey gonk! On the sidewalk! Don't make me say it again!
Outta my fuckin' way. Now!
Choombatta!
Back already? Did ya miss us that bad?
Like I'd miss you fuckheads at all. Nah, biz fell flat. NC folks are a different fuckin' species. Total waste of time.
Heh, sure. Well, welcome home.
You! Where the hell you goin'?
Home…
No such thing, shitstain. Border's closed. Don't want you here.
Me? Don't want me?
Fuckin' glitchin' or somethin'? Yeah, you. Dogtown's off limits to ya.
Since when?
Since you fucked my Nick over. Shit-for-brains didn't even notice, but I did. Not about to let that slide.
I don't know your input! I didn't haze a fuckin' soul!
Nah, just dropped some worthless shit on 'im without batting an eye.
We scan all our stuff! Coulda come and said so if something was borked. Hell'm I s'posed to do now?
Turn your ass around, go back to the city, or stand here till you die. Don't care. Only thing you're not doin' is enterin' Dogtown.
Can't go back, Tygers are on me, took up a contract.
Not my Tygers, not my circus. Go haze 'em like you did us.
It's Dogtown, let 'er go.
Know what? Fuck your zone, fuck your... your…
Parking garage, go. And try not to turn any heads, right?
Fuck! Ugh, she's gettin' away!
Augh, man, I was gonna fuck off early today, too…
Or till we find her. Quit moanin', get the cams up and online.
entries.maleVariant: Or till we find him. Quit moanin', get the cams up and online.

entries.femaleVariant: Careful. They know you're here, might be looking.
Watch… ugh, we'll be here tomorrow still.
[Push]
Mapped your position... Wow. Not bad at all.
Our hands are tied. Don't let it get to you.
C'mon. Broseph's on me.
What the... !?
You alive?
Think so.
Heh, nice. Uh, tell Madam President I said, uh, hey.
entries.maleVariant: Haha, nice. Tell Madam President I said, uh... hey.

entries.femaleVariant: Tell her I said hello.
You got it.
Not everything, though, and not all of 'em…
Hansen was an officer, Militech. Tail end of the Unification War, his unit was tasked with taking Night City.
Traded one conflict for another, basically.
Hot or cold – no better way to make a buck than war.
Kurt Hansen – what's his story?
How'd you land this gig?
Songbird? Nah, nick's not settin' off buzzers.
What about you? Tell me somethin'?
So, seems like a life-long gig you've got. How'd you get recruited? Midnight meet on the East Bay Bridge? Encrypted posts on a local BBS?
Stakes were high, options few.
Pure ambition.
Konpeki was pure ambition. Sometimes you hit a rut in life, wanna blaze your way out.
Do somethin' you'll be remembered for.
entries.maleVariant: Do something you'll be remembered for.

entries.femaleVariant: By the way... Must've gotten old by now, haulin' a faded rockerboy around. Strikes me as tiring…
Heard about a choom, had a blade stuck in his faceplate come the end of a gig.
V? President Myers wishes you the best of luck.
You need to hang tight for a sec.
Seem to have a little time. Care to spare a few detes? 'Bout yourself?
Well, phoo... I'm a Capricorn.
So, what... that make you stubborn? Or you intimating you buy into that hippie dippie star scop?
No idea why it popped into my head now. Guess it meant somethin' to me once…
Now, look for a maintenance room.
[Move]
All this really safe?
It is, it is. Fear not, V.
Tread carefully. Can't estimate if that'll hold your weight, especially remotely.
V! The President needs your help!
Fucking motherfucking fuck!
Pray we don't meet again, and I mean ever.
Preem work, thanks.
Hmm – Biotechnica in sixty-three or four. Fermentation facility in Oregon, off the grid hack. Sound familiar?
Y'know, tough to say... But even if somethin' has changed, I wouldn't know it, right?
Huh. And that's either strangely comforting or fucking terrifying.
Tough to say.
What?
Congrats, V. You just killed Rosalind Myers and fucked the NUSA.
V! There's no time!
Whatcha got in the back?
So... can I go? Kind of in a hurry here.
The usual. Implant boxes, Zetatech.
Headin' for the Longshore Stacks?
Know what? No. Don't know you, don't like your face.
But they're... they'll zero me...
C'mon, Sarah... No point, le'ss roll.
No can do. But you both can fuck off.
Back up to the city line, porkchops. This zone's outside your beat.
Listen to your partner. Talkin' a lotta sense.
I'm NCPD – in pursuit of a suspect who just fled into Dogtown!
[Get in]
[Get out]
You'll be in Dogtown in a minute. Try to steer clear of Hansen's goons.
Refused to demobilize, lay down their weapons. Founded Dogtown instead.
Yeah, where else? They come empty, leave full.
Shit, whole city'll be drownin' in fakes, hm?
Look, I'm just a choom drivin' boxes around.
Hmmm, fair enough...
They? Who's they?
Petrochem! Please... I need in. For a couple of weeks.
Ah. Fugitive suit, running from a hit?
Got anyone inside? Somebody who'd vouch for ya?
I, uh... no.
In three weeks? Take your sob shit somewhere else.
Hit the bricks, city boy.
An' I give zero shits.
Please, three weeks. You'll get your eddies then, I swear!
Hm, yeah, sensin' a buzzer…
No shit – Biotechnica? Enough to make even Bartmoss blush.
You should be one level lower. Eyes peeled, look for a way down.
Yeah, I know the feeling. But ambition, confidence – they're not bad in themselves.
No. Their human toll can be.
Reminds me of when I was starting out. I'd look for places like this... set up a power bypass, jack in, essentially steal my way onto the Net.
Hear a faint buzz.
But you're nowhere near impressed.
No, no, this is my impressed face.
That paranoid clown? Please. Sure hope I don't wind up packed in a fridge standing, psh, who-knows-where.
I happen to know where – garbage dump in the Badlands.
If I'd wanted fame, I'da gone rockerchick.
Ugh… huh?
Still with us?
Augh, what the... what happened?
Your presidential rescue op – miserable failure. Honestly, though? Good fuckin' riddance.
Huh, ugh, OK... So now what?
Huh. We go on livin', start by findin' us a drink.
Daaaghhh…!
Set my sights too high, I guess.
Hah, interesting approach. Had somethin' else in mind, but... you do you.
All right… It's clear you know your way around a deck. Leave you to it.
Ugh, they'll zero you!
V! What're you doing?!
Garage! Run!
S'posed to hack! Quietly!
Well... really hanker for a smoke sometimes…
Sometimes need a smoke – only thing I've noticed.
Huh. That seems... mild in the extreme, at least to me.
Got a last wish – I trip, fall and end up a wet, dead spot down below, call Vik Vektor. Least someone'll pick up my body.
Sure thing, assumin' I get off this plane alive, then survive Dogtown. Really counting on you, V...
How's she doin'?
How's she doin'?
You get used to it.
Not a Silverhand fan, are you?
entries.maleVariant: Not a Silverhand fan, are ya?

entries.femaleVariant: Please. Samurai was done by their second album.
Kept it. Said it gave him "character."
Speakin' of Kurt Hansen – what else you know about 'im?
For a friend.
Don't wanna talk about it.
Garage is huuuuge.
It needed to be. Dogtown was to be the "Pearl of Pacifica" at some point.
A fully automated parking garage with twenty-four thousand spots. Or so went the plan.
Never happened, clearly. Investors took their eddies and ran.
Fuck, depressing.
Big dreams don't fade. They sag and crumble.
Had a friend. We worked together.
Gig was important to him, and he, uh...
He was important to you.
He... didn't make it?
He did not.
Lotsa different reasons…
Uh-huh, like?
Look, uh... no offense, but...
You don't feel like talkin' about it.
Regret it?
Read the room, Songbird.
Maybe.
V, about the construct, is it... I mean, ya feel you're making your own choices?
On your toes, now, guards're riled. Likely after your little show at the gate…
I laid out the details of our plan. Typical Rosalind. "Keep me apprised," she says calmly.
Just sittin' there, sippin' her gin, flickin' through her agenda, postponin' meets.
This is Kurt Hansen. You are now in Dogtown.
Rule two – no corps! You're just not welcome!
Rule one – no NCPD! Badges'll get a bullet to the brain!
Rule three – my people keep the peace in the district and ensure its security. They are the law.
Follow the rules or face the consequences.
You need a dressin' down, too? Piss off.
Moral of the story? Peeps get used to all sorts of shit.
Anything I'd find on BBS gossip feeds?
Hah, neither, nor anything like 'em. Guess you could say I hit the edge, nearly fell over it. First time in my life, I think – definitely not last.
Well, I am stubborn. Do I buy it? Dunno... had a good friend who did.
Woman's unshakeable.
Awful nice of you to ask.
Seem pretty chill, considerin' all hell's about to break loose.
Do I? Guess those years of field ops training didn't go to waste.
They managed to secure a foothold in this southmost pocket and... stuck around.
OOOK... too soon, I guess.
No pressure, we can come back to it.
Eh, grant you that, let's not lose focus.
Better they avoided me.
Goons should be the ones avoidin' me.
You're on Hansen's turf now, don't forget. They rule the roost.
Garage – there, past the fence, see it? Smugglers used to use it – now it's your turn.
Try to sneak in. Maybe distract the guards. I dunno, something.
Great, now in you go. Look for a Net access point. Jack in that, and I'll be able to help you.
Got an access point, but no power.
Hm, see if you can restore it. It's the only way I can be of any use to you.
OK, we're up.
Perfect. Breaching systems now.
Turned somethin' on.
Nice, V. Exactly what we need.
Go back to the access point, jack in with your personal.
Just don't let the bogeymen nab you.
Heh, hang on. OK, Relic hack first, then you slapped a muzzle on Johnny, now you bring some pile of scrap metal back to life?
entries.maleVariant: Hang on. OK, Relic hack first, then you slapped a muzzle on Johnny, now you bring some pile of scrap metal back to life?

entries.femaleVariant: Hmm, ancient, no proto-ancient protocols, largely corrupted data... Gimme a sec, need to ping one of our sats.
Let's see which active Dogtown network links to this infrastructure. Aaaand, puttin' in a back door…
Ready to roll.
Serious trickery, all. Who taught you?
And they took me on 'cause around age thirteen I got the local ripper to sell me a beat-up old deck. Barely left the Net since. I got noticed, the rest is history.
I got a feelin' story's incomplete. Likely longer, more twisted.
entries.maleVariant: Got a feelin' story's incomplete. Likely longer, more twisted.

entries.femaleVariant: Mm? Might be.
No, V... Never been anything like right now.
Got a "Konpeki" of your own?
What about your "Konpeki"? A turnin' point that transformed your life. Ever hit one like that?
Sure, yeah. Militech datafort. Me at seventeen... Hm, or was it nineteen? Breached it via Militech's Ankara base.
Smooth as silk up to a point... Then NetWatch grabbed me. There I was, teetering on the edge. One wrong move and... well, you know.
Kinda like right now, huh?
For now, follow them.
Grabbed the riskiest gigs I could find, learnin' as I went – the hard way, usually. But sometimes, a few times... I really pulled off coups.
V, I'm an NUS intelligence analyst. Trained under the best peeps in the biz.
Bit like right now, huh?
Care to tell me about it?
Sure, sometime. Promise.
[Jack in]
[Enter]
Hang on...
Oh shit!
Uh-huh…
